{
  "stem": "11089.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- they wouldn't-- they wouldn't even hardly talk to a person who went to one of those Zionist groups.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or like myself, I had difficulties to go to Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The only way-- I mean, my father went to the rabbi to ask, can he send me and my sisters, the biggest-- I mean, two years younger sister-- to go to a Zionist school.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The answer was, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "No way.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In fact, they threatened my father, put him into a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] means isolation, out of the camp, the Jewish camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But finally, my uncle-- my-- my mother's brother-- who was in the [YIDDISH], he was going into these Zionistic groups, he kind of backed my father to let me go to Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the only condition was that I can go, but I must come every four weeks to my rabbi, to his office, and he is going to test me.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I must learn the same Talmud, the same everything what they learn it in the yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I must have my payos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I put my payos under my ears, because it was a Zionist school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I had to come home and go to the rabbi, [NON-ENGLISH], and he was testing me exactly what they learned in the yeshiva in Munkacs.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I could not go into the yeshiva, into the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They wouldn't let me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they would stone me, probably.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I couldn't go in there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I had to learn the same.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, my father, as I mentioned, he has the money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He hired for me a tutor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a right hand of the rabbi of Munkacs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he taught me the same-- the same material as they learned in yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the only way I could to go to school.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
